post_text:
First Day Update: Thank you to all of our wonderful students, parents and staff for a very successful first day of school. We had our halls and classrooms graced with many happy students and the positivity could be felt throughout the building.

Just an update on Dismissal Doors:

Door # 1 (Main Entrance) - PreK Ms. Prosser & PreK Ms. Arbore at 12:15; Mrs. Golembiewski & Mrs. Montana at 12:20

Door #2 (Left of the Main Entrance) - Gr. 4 Mrs. McBain at 12:15; Gr. K Mrs. Ciafardini at 12:20,

Door # 5 (Hill) - Gr. 6 Mr. Mahoney & Mr. Tariff at 12:15; Gr. 3 Mrs. Cusson at 12:20

Door # 7 (Flagpole) - Gr. 5 Miss Lebel at 12:15; Gr. 1 Mrs. Tariff at 12:20

Door # 8 (Highway 36) - Gr. 2 Ms. Culp at 12:15; Gr. 2 Ms. Kelly at 12:20

Have a great Highlands Night!

HIGHLANDS ELEMENTARY VIRTUAL LEARNER LUNCH PRE-ORDER F
THIS FORM IS TO BE USED ONLY BY PARENTS/ GUARDIANS OF STUDENTS ENROLLED IN HES COMPLETE REMOTE LEARNING
THIS FORM IS DUE EVERY MONDAY BY 3:00PM
SEPTEMBER 8TH- NOVEMBER 2ND MENU
ORDERING/ PICK UP INSTRUCTIONS
Virtual Learner meal pick up will be at HES on Monday's and Thursday's, 12:30pm-2:30pm
If school is closed on Monday, the pick up will be scheduled for the following Tuesday.
Please use this pre-order form to place your orders for the week (Link below).
https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1hQxmlqwDanjPTjl0ubNNbD2aeQSc6o0_SGSzqNMCT50/edit#gid=0
Lunch for Monday, Tuesday, and Wednesday will be distributed on Monday. The options are shown under Monday on the menu.
Lunch for Thursday and Friday will be distributed on Thursday. The options are shown under Thursday on the menu.
If pick up is scheduled for Tuesday instead of Monday, there will be two lunch options available.
If you have any questions, please email Jessica at jnasto@maschiofood.com

post_text:
Just some reminders from HES...
1) In person learning is scheduled for Mondays, Tuesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays from 8:15 to 12:15 PM (Virtual Learners at Home will be in the PM on these days)
2) Wednesdays are Virtual Learning for ALL STUDENTS (Teachers will provided scheduling)
3) Students should not be dropped off before 8:05 am (There is no supervision until 8:05).
4) The updated "Virtual Calendar" can be found on our website. The link has been provided below.
http://hes.tridistrict.org/UserFiles/Servers/Server_121995/Image/Administration/Calendar/HES%202020-2021%20Virtual%20Calendar%20(FINAL)%20for%20BOE%20Approval.pdf

post_text:
Happy Independence Day!
Over the years, the political importance of this holiday has declined, but Independence Day remains an important national holiday and a symbol of patriotism.
The Fourth of July—also known as Independence Day or July 4th—has been a federal holiday in the United States since 1941. On July 2nd, 1776, the Continental Congress voted in favor of independence, and two days later delegates from the 13 colonies adopted the Declaration of Independence, a historic document drafted by Thomas Jefferson. From 1776 to the present day, July 4th has been celebrated as the birth of American independence.

shared_text:
Henry Hudson Regional School District
May 28 at 7:13 AM ·

Marykate Sharkey, President of the 9th grade class, had a brilliant idea for the Student Council members. She asked her peers and her advisors, Mrs. Fitzsimmons and Ms. DeSanto, if the students could film themselves reading a children's book and then share this with the two elementary schools, Atlantic Highlands and Highlands Elementary Schools. We are sure the children in both schools loved the idea. Here are a few of the videos created by three of our Student Council leaders:
Maeve Sherlock, Layla Ilarraza and President of the Senior Class, Louise Nastasi. Enjoy and share them with your children! #AdmiralPride

post_text: Here are some great pictures that were taken by our amazing PTO while dropping off our 6th grade graduating classes custom lawn signs!
shared_text:
Highlands Elementary School PTO
May 15 at 8:15 PM ·

The PTO would like to take a minute to congrat our graduating class of 2020! I know this is not how we all thought your years at Highlands Elementary School would end! Today we spent the day visiting all your houses and it was so nice to see all of your smiling faces. I hope you all found a little bit of sunshine and happiness with your gifts!

I think of you all as my own children! We spent alot of extra hours together through my time on the PTO, all the play practices, talent shows etc. Most of my afternoons were spent with the class of 2020! I know you all will do great things and I will miss you! Love. MRS. NOBILE

Highlands Elementary School PTO
May 15 at 8:15 PM ·

The PTO would like to take a minute to congrat our graduating class of 2020! I know this is not how we all thought your years at Highlands Elementary School would end! Today we spent the day visiting all your houses and it was so nice to see all of your smiling faces. I hope you all found a little bit of sunshine and happiness with your gifts!

I think of you all as my own children! We spent alot of extra hours together through my time on the PTO, all the play practices, talent shows etc. Most of my afternoons were spent with the class of 2020! I know you all will do great things and I will miss you! Love. MRS. NOBILE

coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19)
What is coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19)?
Coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19) is a respiratory illness
that can spread from person to person. The virus that causes
COVID-19 is a novel coronavirus that was first identified
during an investigation into an outbreak in Wuhan, China.

post_text: Thank you to Mr. DiLorenzo our school Social Worker for arranging to have Monmouth Cares Come out and present the Nurtured Heart Approach to our staff at today’s faculty meeting. Today, teachers role played different ways to respond to students who present with challenging behaviors. Teachers were exposed to positive deescalation strategies in an effort to counteract misbehavior while smoothly transitioning the child back into the instruction taking place.

post_text: Today the HES Green Team hosted, along with The Reclamation Division of the Monmouth County Department of Public Works & Engineering, a Waste Audit and Assembly for our entire school! Thank you to all the students and teachers who participated in today’s Waste Audit!

post_text: All week long at HES our CST brought the staff and students some holiday spirit! Each day the staff with the help of the students were provided a clue to find Code-y (Special Education Code) our Elf. Since Code-y was new to HES he struggled with social and emotional adjustments. With the help of students and staff, Code-y is doing very well and loves his new school. This was such an amazing idea to help educate our students and staff on the struggles of adjustment to new situations. A special thank you goes out to our School Social Worker, Mr. James DiLorenzo and our LDTC Ms. Samantha D’Andrea for coming up with and planning this weeks fun! Congrats to the winning staff who received the gift that keeps on giving...Dunkin Gift Cards! Happy Holidays from our HES family to yours!

post_text:
Atlantic Highlands Historical Society Presents Its Annual Evening of Holiday Music Featuring the Henry Hudson Regional A Cappella Choir
Wednesday December 18

The Atlantic Highlands Historical Society will host its annual Holiday Concert at the Strauss Mansion Museum on Wednesday Dec.18.
Musical Director, Mr. Jeff Starr will conduct the Henry Hudson Regional A Capella choir in an evening of festive songs celebrating the Holiday season.
The museum will open at 7:00 pm and the concert will begin at 7:30 PM. Come enjoy the sites of the Holiday at the beautifully decorated Strauss Mansion Museum and join us for an evening of music and merriment.
Program is free and open to the public. An assortment of Holiday refreshments will be served.
The Strauss Mansion Museum is located at 27 Prospect Circle in Atlantic Highlands.

post_text: HES Food Drive: We had so many people participate in the Highlands Elementary School Student Council Food Drive! Our school collected over 500 items - all of which were donated to the Back Pack Crew Organization! Thank you to all who donated and to our Student Council Advisors Mrs. Ciafardini and Mrs. McBain for organizing this student driven project! Special congratulations goes out to Mr. Conrad’s class for donating the most items! Additionally, we would like to congratulate Mrs. Golembiewski’s and Mrs. Montana’s for donating the most items per student! Have a Happy Thanksgiving!

shared_text:
Henry Hudson Regional School District
November 27, 2019 at 6:41 AM ·

Congratulations to Corina Vidal for accepting a full athletic scholarship from the University of Rhode Island! This is exciting news for Henry Hudson as Corina is the second Division 1 Athlete to officially sign to run track and cross country in the past 10 years! The administration, coaches and staff are all proud of Corina's amazing career at HHRS and wish her all the best as she moves on to the collegiate level! #AdmiralPride

post_text:
Attention Parents/Guardians and Student-Athletes:

All students need a physical from a medical doctor as well as all the necessary paperwork (on athletic page on website) in order to participate in sports at HHRS. In an effort to help you, HHRS Board of Education provides two days of FREE sports physicals conducted by our school physician and nursing staff.

If you would like to take advantage of this opportunity, they are scheduled for July 24, 2019 from 12-4 pm. and July 25, 2019 from 2-6 pm at HHRS. If you are unable to get to this free opportunity, you will need to have your own doctor provide the necessary examination and paperwork.

Students going into grade 5 and 6 in September are eligible for a number of sports at the middle school. You are required to get a sports physical and fill out all the necessary forms in order to participate.

To All Highlands Elementary School Parents (Grades 1-6)

We are rolling out the red carpet once again for the Highlands Elementary School's fourth marking period awards. The ceremony will be held on Tuesday, June 18th, 2019, in the All Purpose Room (APR). If your child has earned High Honor Roll, Honor Roll, or has met the requirements for Citizenship, he/she will be receiving an award on this day. Please note that a parent letter is only sent home to parents for marking periods 1-3, but a phone blast will be sent out by Monday, 6/17/2019 to notify you if your child will be recieving an award. All parents/guardians are invited to attend. Please see the awards schedule below. 6th grade MP awards will be issued on the night of the 6th Promotion.

1st Grade through 6th Grade @ 9:00 AM

We are looking forward to seeing everybody there. Please be advised that you should arrive a few minutes earlier than the start time in order to have plenty of time to sign in and get your seat.Be sure to have proper photo ID, or you may not be able to enter the buliding.

post_text: This is an important message from New Jersey American Water. New Jersey American Water will begin routine flushing of the water distribution system in your area Monday, June 03 thru Tuesday, June 04 from 8:00 A.M. to 4:00 P.M. to ensure that you continue to receive high-quality water service. Flushing also allows us to monitor and maintain fire hydrants. When crews are working in your area, you may notice reduced pressure, cloudy and or discolored water. If your water is discolored, run the cold water only at the lowest level of the house for about 3 to 5 minutes so that it clears before using. Repeat this flushing step once or twice within an hour as necessary until the water clears. For more information log on to our website at www.newjerseyamwater.com, and select Alert Notifications.

Please remember the words of John F. Kennedy when he said “My fellow Americans, ask not what your country can do for you, ask what you can do for your country.”
Well, that’s just what the men and women serving our country did. They gave the ultimate sacrifice to preserve the freedom that we all enjoy today, and that’s what we will forever memorialize.
On Behalf of all the staff and administration, have a great Memorial Day, and never forget!

post_text:
The Highlands Elementary School's annual Co-operation Day (Field Day) will be held on Tuesday, May 21st, 2019. All students in Pre-Kindergarten through 6th grade will participate in a number of activities. Please remind your child to bring the following items:
• Sneakers (no sandals or flip flops)
• Play Clothes
• Water Bottle (with your child's initials on it)
• Towel
• Sunscreen
• A Hat or Visor
• Extra set of clothes in case you get wet.
If you are planning to be a spectator at this event, please remember the following information:
• No smoking is permitted on school grounds
• Keep preschoolers or small children with you at all times
• Remain only in the spectator area (At the top of the hill)
Only pre-approved volunteers will be allowed to participate in activities.
Pre K through 2nd grade participates from 9:00 AM to 11:30 AM
and 3rd grade to 6th grade participates from 12:35 PM to 2:30 PM.
If you have any questions please contact the main office at 732-872-1476 Extension 10.
